\u00d7 is an accrual red flag.","why_it_can_fail":"One-off working-capital swings or a capex year can distort a single ratio; the 5-yr median smooths it."},{"label":"Balance-sheet safety","value":0.24,"unit":"\u00d7 D/E","status":"good","read":"Conservatively financed (D/E 0.24\u00d7, interest cover 10.4\u00d7).","meaning":"Latest debt-to-equity and interest coverage (EBIT \u00f7 interest) from the balance sheet.","why_useful":"Low debt and high interest cover let a business survive a downturn; high debt amplifies trouble.","why_it_can_fail":"Off-balance-sheet leases/guarantees aren't captured; a cash-rich firm can show low D/E yet still be risky elsewhere."},{"label":"Earnings momentum","value":-10.66,"unit":"% YoY","status":"weak","read":"Profit down 11% YoY (latest TTM).","meaning":"Trailing-twelve-month net profit vs the year-ago TTM (and whether the YoY rate is rising = 'accelerating').","why_useful":"Improving, accelerating earnings tend to drive re-rating; falling profit warns of a deteriorating business.","why_it_can_fail":"TTM can be lumpy for cyclicals/one-offs; cross-check the multi-year trend on the Fundamentals tab."}]},"valuation":{"ok":true,"is_bank":false,"pe_now":61.6,"pe_percentile":74.0,"median_pe":47.7,"earnings_yield_pct":1.62,"pb":9.99,"ev_ebitda":37.71,"quality_score":84.0,"pat_cagr_5y_pct":39.2,"peg":1.57,"cheapness":{"status":"weak","read":"P/E at the 74-percentile of its 10-yr range \u2014 expensive vs its own history."},"expectations":"At 61.6\u00d7 earnings for ~39% 5-yr profit CAGR, the market is paying \u22481.57\u00d7 growth (PEG). >2 = a lot already priced in; <1 = cheap if growth holds. This PEG divides TTM P/E by TRAILING 5-year annual PAT CAGR (endpoint-to-endpoint) \u2014 a time-axis mismatch vs the textbook FORWARD-EPS PEG, and one abnormal base/terminal year distorts the CAGR. A rough trailing valuation-vs-growth gauge, not a precise forward PEG.","cyclical_caveat":null,"meaning":"P/E percentile = where today's price-to-earnings sits within the stock's own last-10-yr range (low = cheap vs its past). Paired with the Quality score and 5-yr profit growth so a cheap multiple is judged against business strength, not in isolation.","why_useful":"Cheapness only matters relative to quality and growth \u2014 a low P/E on a declining or peak-cyclical business is a trap, not a bargain.","why_it_can_fail":"P/E breaks for loss-makers / one-offs; for banks use P/B not EV/EBITDA; a multiple cheap vs history can stay cheap if the business has structurally de-rated."},"ownership":{"ok":true,"na":null,"holders":{"Promoter":{"periods":["Jun 2023","Sep 2023","Dec 2023","Mar 2024","Jun 2024","Sep 2024","Dec 2024","Mar 2025","Jun 2025","Sep 2025","Dec 2025","Mar 2026"],"values":[38.91,36.49,36.5,36.5,36.53,36.46,36.46,36.47,36.48,36.48,36.48,36.48],"latest_pct":36.48,"chg_1y_pp":0.01},"FII":{"periods":["Jun 2023","Sep 2023","Dec 2023","Mar 2024","Jun 2024","Sep 2024","Dec 2024","Mar 2025","Jun 2025","Sep 2025","Dec 2025","Mar 2026"],"values":[11.06,14.89,15.38,15.93,17.04,18.06,18.48,16.94,16.21,16.05,14.66,13.8],"latest_pct":13.8,"chg_1y_pp":-3.14},"DII":{"periods":["Jun 2023","Sep 2023","Dec 2023","Mar 2024","Jun 2024","Sep 2024","Dec 2024","Mar 2025","Jun 2025","Sep 2025","Dec 2025","Mar 2026"],"values":[24.51,25.24,24.82,24.69,23.56,22.84,22.19,23.13,23.37,25.32,26.76,27.78],"latest_pct":27.78,"chg_1y_pp":4.65},"Public":{"periods":["Jun 2023","Sep 2023","Dec 2023","Mar 2024","Jun 2024","Sep 2024","Dec 2024","Mar 2025","Jun 2025","Sep 2025","Dec 2025","Mar 2026"],"values":[25.54,23.39,23.29,22.89,22.85,22.63,22.86,23.44,23.91,22.12,22.08,21.92],"latest_pct":21.92,"chg_1y_pp":-1.52}},"pledge":null,"events":[{"date":"19-Jul-2024","subject":"Dividend - Rs 7 Per Share","materiality":"Low"},{"date":"18-Jul-2025","subject":"Dividend - Rs 9 Per Share","materiality":"Low"},{"date":"17-Jul-2026","subject":"Dividend - Rs 8.50 Per Share","materiality":"Low"}],"placeholders":[{"label":"Promoter pledge (detail)","note":"